<P>
   MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - There is no rush to an actual letter.
It's made slowly and travels slowly. Not computer mail. A letter
that is shipped in an instant and received in an instant carries
with it the expectation of instantaneous response. This isn't
possible for someone like me, whose mind clops along the
information super highway like an Amish horse and buggy. BY E.J.
MONTINI. Story will move in the ``K'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-27-00 0802EDT &QL; 
