<SLUG> BC-ONE-A-DAY-MED-BRIEF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DOES YOUR DOCTOR FEEL YOUR PAIN?  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;    (This premium feature from The New York Times Syndicate is
available without charge to clients of this news wire.)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    
 By SAM URETSKY  
 c.2000 HealthScout.com  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by The New York Times Syndicate) &LR;  &QL;
<P>
   In spite of all the progress that's been made in pain management
over the years, narcotic painkillers are still the best drugs for
severe pain. But many doctors _ fearing patient addiction or action
from government regulators _ are reluctant to prescribe narcotics.
So some patients suffer needlessly.
</P>
<P>
   University of Texas researchers surveyed medical students to
find out which were most reluctant to order narcotics for pain
relief. Those most likely to have opiophobia _ fear of prescribing
narcotics _ had three common traits:
</P>
<P>
   -- They were most likely to rely on high tech equipment.
</P>
<P>
   -- They were most subject to outside control.
</P>
<P>
   -- They didn't like to make decisions if they weren't sure of
the outcomes.
</P>
<P>
   So if you go to a doctor who doesn't like to take chances, you
may be left in pain. But does that mean you're better off with one
who doesn't mind taking risks? Maybe this matter requires a second
opinion.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT HEALTHSCOUT:
</P>
<P>
   HealthScout (http://www.healthscout.com) is a service of Rx
Remedy, Inc., a leader in the field of health information and
publisher of REMEDY Magazine, a prize-winning health publication
read in 2.2 American homes.
</P>
<P>
   -- All of HealthScout's original stories are based on primary
sources: reports in refereed medical journals and interviews with
the medical researchers who authored them. Fact-checkers
independently confirm reporters' work on sensitive stories.
</P>
<P>
   -- HealthScout's medical writers and editors have previously
worked at many of the nation's most respected newspapers and
magazines.
</P>
<P>
   -- HealthScout's Scientific Advisory Board includes leading
authorities in more than a dozen disciplines.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
