<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    GRAPEVINE: News, notes from the wrestling industry
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The big news this week is the World Wrestling Federation's move
to The Nashville Network.
</P>
<P>
   Monday night's ``Raw is War'' made its debut on TNN and the
television ratings did not waver much.
</P>
<P>
   After last week's 5.9, this week's 5.4 is pretty strong for the
jump from USA Network, which had been the Monday night home for the
WWF for five years.
</P>
<P>
   World Championship Wrestling's ``Nitro'' show had slightly
higher (2.9 compared to 2.8) ratings as a result of the change and
a strong show. The return of Lex Luger and Ric Flair, along with a
Goldberg-Scott Steiner cage match were strong draws, but could not
keep the WCW rating from dipping nearly one whole ratings point
from the 8 p.m. to 9 p.m. time slot.
</P>
<P>
   WWF's ``Raw'' debut was also strong with the major return of
``Stone Cold'' Steve Austin and a pay-per-view quality ladder match
between Edge and Christian and the Hardy Boyz.
</P>
<P>
   _ WCW star Kevin Nash will be taking a break from in-ring
wrestling for a few weeks to rehabilitate his injured knee. He was
scheduled to have surgery after ``Fall Brawl,'' but he will rest
for a few weeks and continue as the coach for the Natural Born
Thrillers.
</P>
<P>
   _ A return of the ECW Triple Threat of Tazz, Raven and Saturn
could be in the works for the WWF. Raven's move to the WWF allows
for the three ECW stars to finally get a foothold on the WWF turf.
</P>
<P>
   _ Exiled WWF star Mark Henry may return from a stint in the WWF
minors as soon as the ``Survivor Series.'' Henry has been working
on losing weight in an attempt to improve his in-ring movements.
</P>
<P>
   _ Another WWF star who is working on the fat farm is the Big
Show. It was hoped he would return soon as the man who ran over
Austin, but it doesn't look like he can stay away from the dinner
table long enough to shed a few pounds.
</P>
<P>
   _ Billy Gunn was not backstage at either ``Unforgiven'' or
``Raw'' and his return may be delayed as he recovers from rotator
cuff surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
