 &HT;    With GLENN-MATH.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   U.S. RANKINGS IN MATH AND SCIENCE TESTS
</P>
<P>
   General Science
</P>
<P>
   Fourth-graders .... third among 26 nations
</P>
<P>
   Eighth-graders ..... 17th among 41 nations
</P>
<P>
   Twelfth-graders .... 18th among 20 nations
</P>
<P>
   Mathematics
</P>
<P>
   Fourth-graders .... 12th among 26 nations
</P>
<P>
   Eighth-graders ..... 28th among 41 nations
</P>
<P>
   Twelfth-graders .... 18th among 20 nations
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS WITH TOO FEW QUALIFIED MATH AND SCIENCE TEACHERS
</P>
<P>
   In the average school district:
</P>
<P>
   High schools ...... 61 percent
</P>
<P>
   Middle schools ... 48 percent
</P>
<P>
   In urban school districts:
</P>
<P>
   High schools ....... 95 percent
</P>
<P>
   Middle schools .... 80 percent
</P>
<P>
   QUESTIONS FOR PARENTS TO ASK
</P>
<P>
   (Suggested by the National Commission on Mathematics and Science
Teaching for the 21st Century)
</P>
<P>
   Do the math and science achievement levels at your child's
school compare favorably to achievement level in neighboring
schools?
</P>
<P>
   Do your child's teachers have the necessary background to teach
the courses to which they are assigned?
</P>
<P>
   How does the teacher salary schedule in your school district
compare to that of neighboring districts?
</P>
<P>
   If you are not satisfied with the answers to any of these
questions, the following checklist can help promote higher student
achievement:
</P>
<P>
   _ Learn about the math and science standards that children are
required to meet in your state and get a clear picture of how well
your child's school is doing in meeting these standards.
</P>
<P>
   _ Support the principal's efforts to hire well-qualified
teachers and to provide them with opportunities to continually
improve their skills.
</P>
<P>
   _ Support increased funding for programs that support quality
math and science teaching.
</P>
<P>
   Source: ``Before It's Too Late, a Report to the Nation from the
National Commission on Mathematics and Science Teaching for the
21st Century.''
</P>
<P>
   For a copy of the full report, call toll-free 1-877-ED-PUBS or
access www.ed.gov/americacounts/glenn
</P>
