<P>
   BUSINESS
</P>
<P>
   INTERACTIVE-TV _ WASHINGTON _ In a testy House Commerce
subcommittee hearing dominated by each side airing complaints about
the other, AOL head Steve Case and Time Warner Chief Gerald Levin
promised again Wednesday to allow open access to cable systems if
their merger is allowed to go through. But they again refused to
make their commitment legally binding. (Geewax, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location Atlanta, category Business, subcategory
Technology.
</P>
<P>
   NETWORLD _ ATLANTA _ Benjamin Netanyahu comes to Networld to
talk telecom. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-CASESALES _ ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola Co. said it expects
third-quarter global case sales to rise 4 percent on recovering
international markets. Coca-Cola gets more than half its sales and
profits outside the U.S. Coca-Cola's case sales were expected to
rise 3 percent to 5 percent in the third quarter, analysts said.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   E-BUSINESS _ A daily column featuring the most useful Web sites
and live online events affecting Business readers. Today: (Seward,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ It's a week for awards. Evan Connell, author of
``Son of the Morning Star,'' has won $100,000 for the prestigious
Lannan Literary Award, and eight other writers have been awarded a
total of $600,000. And, in Atlanta, the Southern Regional Council
has announced the three winners of the Lillian Smith Book Awards.
The recipients are Michael Keith Honey, author of ``Black Workers
Remember''; Andrew M. Manis, author of ``A Fire You Can't Put Out:
the Civil Rights life of Birmingham's Reverend Fred Shuttleworth'';
and Lawrence N. Powell for ``Troubled Memory: Anne Levy, the
Holocaust, and David Duke's Louisiana.'' (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   E-LIVING _ A daily column featuring the most useful Web sites
and live online events affecting arts, entertainment and leisure
activites. Today: (Footlick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (l) Lifestyle and (a) General News categories.)
</P>
