   AUSTRALIAN WINES _ With the Summer Games going on, it might be
an opportune time to try wines from Down Under. (Fisher, Dayton
Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD INFORMATION _ List of places to get cooking and nutritional
information. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-BELGIAN _ When the Crown Prince and Princess of Belgium
announced they'll visit New York this fall, it made the cover page
headlines of the New York Times, in part because Belgium is so in,
especially when it comes to food. The number of Belgian restaurants
in the big apple have jumped from 4 in the early 90s to nearly 20
now. The latest power lunch in Washington is a French/Belgian
bistoro. And Atlanta's first Belgian bistro hit the scene earlier
this year. There's more to the food than waffles and brussel
sprouts. Their twice-fried fries set the standard and mussels are
magnificent. Belgian beers are popping up in bars around, town,
too. w/recipes and sidebar on belgian beer by Bob Townsend.
(Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO and LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-BELGIAN-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with Belgian story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH LAYOUT.
</P>
