workers who feel the company doesn't need them anymore. To a large
extent, they're right. By Ross Kerber. 1050 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Alternative energy stocks pushing
fuel cells and solar power have been hot this year thanks to
electric deregulation and the energy demands of the wired world.
Higher oil prices are only raising the psychic ante. By Steven Syre
and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ He hopes to retire by age 60. Is his
plan feasible? By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
