<HEADLINE>
GREAT GIFTS FOR BOYS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By JAVONNA MAY-MONS 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Recently, we gave you four nifty and thrifty birthday present
ideas for girls _ all less than $15. This week: Boys have their
day. We looked for things other than the usual suspects: baseball
caps, racing cars, dinosaurs, trading cards and the like. Here,
four fab ideas.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   1. MUSIC MAKES THE WORLD GO 'ROUND
</P>
<P>
   Instead of spending almost $20 on a new CD, why not stick with
old favorites? There are dozens of discount CD stores where an old
Aerosmith or Stevie Wonder CD will cost you about $9.99 at most. If
your friends are listening to the A(asterisk)Teens' hot versions of
``Mamma Mia'' and ``Dancing Queen'' (and how can they avoid it?),
give them something to talk about with an original ABBA collection.
Or try the Jackson 5, the original boy band.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   2. OVER AND OUT
</P>
<P>
   Backyard commando-style games wouldn't be complete without the
proper equipment. And, considering that most guys love electronic
gadgets, these walkie-talkies (from the Store of Knowledge) make
the perfect gift. They're great for hours of indoor and outdoor
use, and at $12.99, they're a terrific deal.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   3. DARK KNIGHT
</P>
<P>
   For the older kid who's ``too old'' for action figures but still
loves superheroes, try this Batman pen and key-ring set (Warner
Bros. Studio Store, $7.50). Other favorites such as Superman, Bugs
Bunny and Tweety are available as well. Give your backpack a new
midsemester look with one of these swinging key rings.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   4. OLDIE BUT GOODIE
</P>
<P>
   Sometimes the usual suspects can be a good thing. Boys can't
have too many footballs, can they? But instead of the regular
pigskin, try a slight change, like a ``sure-grip'' football and
``turbine tail-fin'' football, both from Zoam (KB Toys, $11.99).
They're great for backyard tossing, and they tear through the air
like rockets _ a big plus with boys. Other classic toys will do the
trick as well: a basketball, a baseball and bat or a soccer ball.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
