<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, SEPT. 27 
</HEADLINE>
  EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CAMPAIGN-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Monday, September 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, September
25, about gift packages sent to reporters by Marcia Lieberman, the
mother of Senator Joseph I. Lieberman, misspelled the brand of
bagel chips she included. It is Manischewitz, not Manishewitz.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MS-TREATMENT-NYT (moved on Monday, September 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, September
25, about using the drug Avonex (also called interferon beta-1a) to
delay the onset of multiple sclerosis omitted the source of the
research report. It is scheduled for publication tomorrow in The
New England Journal of Medicine.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-SHRIMP-BUBBLES-NYT (moved on Monday, September 25) &QL; 
A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, September 25,
about the sound made by snapping shrimp misidentified the journal
that published the research. It was Science, not Nature.  &QL;
</P>
