Wednesday that former Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will not be
charged in an investigation into corruption allegations. His famous
``time out'' from politics, which he announced after losing in the
1999 election to Ehud Barak, will likely end soon. Netanyahu, the
man Israelis either love or love to hate, was in the United States,
but he is expected to return and start trying to knock off those
that stand in his way _ first Likud Party icon Ariel Sharon and
then, in expected early elections, Barak. (Kaplow, Cox News
Service).
