<P>
   SOUND BYTES: Media critic Norman Chad offered on his Web site,
``The Accidental Cynic,'' a directory of what America's top
sportscasters sound like. Chad's takes on a few you may have heard:
</P>
<P>
   Hubie Brown (TNT): Like arthroscopic surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Skip Caray (TBS): Like a pecan log from Stuckey's.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Costas (NBC): Like the kid in the back of the room in
seventh grade.
</P>
<P>
   Keith Jackson (ABC): Like a steer auctioneer.
</P>
<P>
   Van Earl Wright (Fox Sports Net): Like a pinball machine.
</P>
<P>
   www.accidentalcynic.com
</P>
<P>
   HART'S HEISMAN: Notre Dame great Leon Hart's 1949 Heisman Trophy
is on the auction block at sothebys.amazon.com's Legends of the
Gridiron fall sale. No one had made the $100,000 opening bid as of
Wednesday afternoon, though the trophy has an estimated valued of
$150,000 to $200,000. The site's description of the trophy includes
information on Hart, one of only two linemen to win the award, and
a detailed description of the trophy's condition _ it has worn
corners and six holes around the base from being attached to the
Freedom Train that toured the U.S. in 1976.
</P>
<P>
   sothebys.amazon.com
</P>
<P>
   POWER PLAY: A sports learning software company and a maker of
hockey equipment and related apparel have joined forces online to
teach youngsters about the sport. Samsports.com will become the
official provider of instructional hockey content for
ccmsports.com, which will provide hockey equipment to be used in
filming and production of Samsports' Hockey Without Limits video
series. Featuring former NHL coach Wayne Fleming, the videos, which
can be purchased at Samsports' site, teach fundamentals of skating,
puck handling, passing and shooting. The company also has teaching
series for baseball, golf, soccer and tennis.
</P>
<P>
   www.samsports.com
</P>
<P>
   www.ccmsports.com
</P>
