 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)   &HT;    Hoops, anyone?
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   While soft and squishy sports are often best suited to indoor
play, PlayHut's Shoot A Round basketball contraption ($22;
www.playhut.com functions well in any environment. Essentially a
wire and mesh pop-up box with a hoop, the modestly sized ``portable
basketball court'' practically erects itself (though collapsing the
unit can involve a rich lesson in origami) and comes complete with
four undersized balls. Shooting ``nuthin' but net'' returns a ball
down a funnel flume. Moreover, crashing the boards is an immensely
forgiving endeavor as the Shoot A Round will yield completely and
then sproing itself back into shape. A lot of fun for the whole
family.
</P>
<P>
   _ Shaun Conlin
</P>
