<HEADLINE>
NFL CAPSULES FOR WEEK 5
</HEADLINE>
 CAPSULES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEPHEN SCHROATS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
DALLAS COWBOYS AT CAROLINA PANTHERS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Cowboys 1-3, Panthers 1-2 SERIES: Tied, 1-1 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Cowboys won, 27-20, on Oct. 11, 1998, as Emmitt Smith
rushes for 112 yards and a TD. THE LINE: Panthers by 6 THE SCOOP
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ The Cowboys are the NFL's worst defense against the run,
having allowed 201-yard rushers in each of their two home games,
and are third-worst overall, allowing 379.3 total yards per game.
They are giving up 34 points a game, second-most in the NFL.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Cowboys are the second team in the NFL to allow two
200-yard rushers in the same season, and the other was the 1973 New
England Patriots when O.J. Simpson did it twice against them during
his 2,000-yard rushing season.
</P>
<P>
   _ There were just two 200-yard rushers against Dallas in 594
regular-season games in the team's first 40 seasons, and one of
those was Hall of Famer Jim Brown in 1963.
</P>
<P>
   _ QB Troy Aikman returned as the Dallas starter after missing
two games because of his ninth concussion. He was 14-of-25 passing
for 197 yards with a touchdown, an interception and a fumble.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rookie PK Tim Seder's 40-yard field goal was his sixth
straight to start his Cowboys career, three short of the team
record.
</P>
<P>
   _ Panthers QB Steve Beuerlein, a former Cowboys backup, has
thrown a touchdown in 12 consecutive games.
</P>
<P>
   _ Panthers RB Tim Biakabutuka leads the team with 208 yards
rushing. He trails by 120 yards the late Fred Lane's team career
record of 2,001.
</P>
<P>
   _ Panthers TE Wesley Walls has a 64-game receiving streak. THE
PICK: Christmas in Carolina. Panthers, 33-20.
</P>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO CHARGERS AT ST. LOUIS RAMS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Chargers 0-4, Rams 4-0 SERIES: Tied, 3-3 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Chargers won, 31-17, on Nov. 27, 1994, as Darien Gordon
returns a punt 75 yards for a score. THE LINE: Rams by 17 THE SCOOP
</P>
<P>
   _ Chargers QB Ryan Leaf threw his seventh interception of the
season last week. He has one TD pass. He also has a cast on his
sprained right wrist.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jim Harbaugh is expected to be the third Chargers QB to start
a game this season.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Chargers have scored one touchdown or less in 35 of their
past 52 games.
</P>
<P>
   _ Of the Rams' 20 touchdowns, eight have come on plays of 60
yards or longer; five are of 80 yards or longer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rams QB Kurt Warner has passed for more than 300 yards 12
times in 19 games. He has 10 TDs and 1,557 yards in a
quarter-season, which projects to 40 TDs and 6,228 yards for 16
games, or 1,144 more yards than Dan Marino's single-season record.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams' defense had eight sacks, two interceptions and two
fumble recoveries, including a 94-yard fumble return by safety
Keith Lyle, against the Falcons.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams increased their scoring average to 40 points per
game. The defending Super Bowl champions have reached 30 points in
an NFL-record 10 consecutive regular-season games. THE PICK:
Scorekeeper better be on the ball. Rams, 45-15.
</P>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS COLTS AT BUFFALO BILLS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Colts 2-1, Bills 2-1 SERIES: Bills lead, 34-24-1 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Bills won, 31-6, on Jan. 2, 2000, as Rob
Johnson throws two TDs to snap the Colts' 11-game winning streak.
THE LINE: Bills by 1 1/2 THE SCOOP
</P>
<P>
   _ The Colts have won in Buffalo only three times since 1980, and
not since 1994.
</P>
<P>
   _ Colts QB Peyton Manning passed for a franchise-record 440
yards and threw TDs to four receivers on Monday. He broke his own
team record of 404 yards set against San Diego on Sept. 26, 1999.
</P>
<P>
   _ The 5-foot-7 WR Terrence Wilkins played for the first time
since suffering a concussion on Aug. 12, and had a career-high nine
receptions and 148 yards.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Colts' defense, which had one sack and one turnover in its
first two games, held Jacksonville scoreless and to a net of 52
yards in the second half.
</P>
<P>
   _ WR Marvin Harrison's 76-yard TD catch was the longest of his
career. He has caught a pass in all 63 of his NFL games, the
second-longest streak in Colts history.
</P>
<P>
   _ The safety by the Colts was their first since Oct. 5, 1997,
against the New York Jets.
</P>
<P>
   _ Manning's four touchdown passes were the most by a Colts
quarterback since Jim Harbaugh had four in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Bills' defense is second in the NFL, holding opponents to
61.3 yards rushing and 180.3 yards passing.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Bills have won eight of their past nine AFC East home
games.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bills RB Antowain Smith has eight TD runs in six career games
against the Colts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bills QB Rob Johnson has at least two TD passes in three of
his past four games. THE PICK: Colts have all the weapons. Colts
28-20.
MINNESOTA VIKINGS AT DETROIT LIONS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Vikings 3-0, Lions 3-1 SERIES: Vikings lead, 47-28-2 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Vikings won, 24-17, on Jan. 2, 2000, as
Randy Moss catches five passes for 155 yards and a TD. THE LINE:
Lions by 1 THE SCOOP
</P>
<P>
   _ The Vikings are one of only three undefeated teams (along with
the 4-0 Jets and 4-0 Rams).
</P>
<P>
   _ The Vikings are 9-2 after bye weeks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Vikings QB Daunte Culpepper has rushed for 169 yards and three
TDs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Vikings WR Randy Moss had 15 catches for 280 yards and two TDs
in two games against the Lions last season.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lions WR Johnnie Morton had 18 catches for 202 yards and two
TDs in two games against the Vikings last season.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Lions have scored an NFC-low four touchdowns, yet only the
Rams and Jets have won more games.
</P>
<P>
   _ James Stewart's 1-yard score was the Lions' first rushing TD
in 21 quarters. THE PICK: Hot Culpepper. Vikings, 33-24.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK GIANTS AT TENNESSEE TITANS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Giants 3-1, Titans 2-1 SERIES: Giants lead, 5-1 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Oilers won, 10-6, on Nov. 9, 1997, as Eddie George rushes
for 122 yards and the game's only TD. THE LINE: Titans by 5 1/2 THE
SCOOP
</P>
<P>
   _ QB Kerry Collins had been sacked only three times in the
Giants' first three games, but was caught four times against the
Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tiki Barber is second in the NFC with 391 yards rushing.
Heisman Trophy winner Ron Dayne's 220 rushing yards leads all
rookies.
</P>
<P>
   _ Barber has already eclipsed last season's Giants leading
rusher, Joe Montgomery with 348 yards.
</P>
<P>
   _ Both Titans victories have come after trailing at the
two-minute warning.
</P>
<P>
   _ WR Carl Pickens had his first 100-yard receiving game with the
Titans, and the 20th of his career.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Titans' pass defense (171 yards per game) tops the AFC.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Titans are 17-2 against the AFC Central since 1998. THE
PICK: Undefeated home streak ends. Giants, 24-21.
</P>
<P>
   BALTIMORE RAVENS AT CLEVELAND BROWNS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Ravens 3-1, Browns 2-2 SERIES: Ravens lead, 2-0 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Ravens won, 41-9, on Nov. 7, 1999, as Errict Rhett rushes
for 117 yards and two TDs. THE LINE: Ravens by 8 1/2 THE SCOOP
</P>
