<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EDS: This version replaces earlier one.
 &HT;    NEWS ABOUT THE NET: 09.28.00
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   _ Knight to star in commercial
</P>
<P>
   _ NBC monitors your monitor
</P>
<P>
   _ Olympic traffic increases
</P>
<P>
   REFORMED CHOKERS: Just when you thought Bob Knight was about to
go away, the world's most famous recently fired college basketball
coach will show his mug on a commercial during the medal round of
Olympic basketball. A rough cut of the footage starring Mr. Knight
_ or Coach Knight _ who guided the 1984 U.S. Olympic basketball
team to the gold medal, appeared from Tuesday until Wednesday
afternoon on HoopsTV.com. The commercial is for sports apparel
company And1, the same company that another famous choker, Latrell
Sprewell, did a commercial for during last year's NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
   www.HoopsTV.com
</P>
<P>
