<HEADLINE>
DAIMLERCHRYSLER INVESTS IN CHINA 
 
</HEADLINE>
  By The New York Times 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SHANGHAI, China _ DaimlerChrysler will invest $118 million in
cash to revive Beijing Jeep, one of the earliest joint ventures in
China that has been making the same modified Jeep for the past 15
years.
</P>
<P>
   The investment is part of a $226 million restructuring plan
meant to prepare the joint venture for competition after China
enters the World Trade Organization and duties on imported sport
utility vehicles fall. DaimlerChrysler plans to produce two new
models at the joint venture in the next three years. China is
expected to join the WTO within the next few months.
</P>
</TEXT>
