Vice President Al Gore, the Democratic presidential candidate,
addresses a crowd of supporters holding up campaign posters during
a campaign rally in downtown Des Moines, Wednesday. During the
rally Gore had harsh words for his Republican opponent Gov. George
W. Bush's Medicare plans, saying Bush's proposals would ``force
seniors to beg'' for prescription drug coverage. (Ruth Fremson/The
