<SLUG> BC-GEN-UNIBEAT-COLUMN-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TENNYSON COMING INTO HIS OWN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Officially, UCLA's men's soccer team plays on
Frank Marshall Field, named after the Hollywood producer who was
part of the Bruins' first NCAA-level team in 1967.
</P>
<P>
   It should be called Tennyson Field. McKinley Tennyson has made
it his own.
</P>
<P>
   The senior forward from Indiana has four goals on the field
(Cliff McKinley has the other) and eight goals this season, ranking
him first nationally in goals per game (1.6) and second in points
per game (3.2) for the 6-0, No. 1-ranked Bruins, who play tonight
at Santa Clara.
</P>
<P>
   Tennyson also has scored back-to-back hat tricks (Sept. 6
against San Diego State and Sept. 17 against San Francisco) _
believed to be the first time it has been done since UNLV's Doug
Borgel in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   And he has done it on a young UCLA team that starts six freshmen
regularly.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm hot right now,'' Tennyson said. ``I'm a forward. I'm
supposed to score goals . . . (and) an inch can mean a goal. I've
scored off some crosses, I'm getting good crosses from Shaun
Tsakiris and Adolfo Gregorio. I've been fortunate.''
</P>
<P>
   Only in some ways.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Todd Saldana knows this is a make-or-break year for
Tennyson. He wasn't part of the under-20 World Cup team, nor did he
play in the Olympics, which is the under-23 world championship.
Saldana knows Tennyson would like to play at the national level, so
he told Tennyson to work on his fitness, strength and ability to
hold onto the ball when defenders pressure.
</P>
<P>
   ``For his size (6-foot-2 and 190 pounds) he should never get
knocked off the ball,'' Saldana said. ``He's always been fast,
always been powerful. He has scored goals before.''
</P>
<P>
   Tennyson's favorite moment came during his freshman year, when
he scored against Indiana in the NCAA-championship game, which UCLA
won.
</P>
<P>
   Since then, he has been a consistent scorer but never as the
first option. When you play alongside forwards such as Seth George
and Sasha Victorine, midfielders look for them first.
</P>
<P>
   They have graduated, leaving Tennyson as the first option. He is
making the most of it.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has that potential and now he's trying to prove it,''
Saldana said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Miscellaneous Troy: One reason USC is ranked No. 1 by
Volleyball Magazine: Jennifer Pahl, who was named Pac-10 player of
the week after hitting .615 in two matches with 16 kills and no
errors in 27 attempts. She also had 10 blocks and eight digs.
</P>
<P>
   But she's not the only one playing well. Janae Henry had 11
kills and 11 digs in the sweep of Stanford on Friday, ending the
Cardinal's home streak at 45 matches and giving USC its first win
at Stanford since 1977.
</P>
<P>
   By sweeping Cal the next night, USC tied a 23-year-old record of
opening the season by winning 27 consecutive games. The Trojans
will break the record if they win the first game against Oregon
State on Friday. A victory in the first !ital!two games would give
this squad the school record for consecutive games won.
</P>
<P>
   USC is 9-0 and one of four undefeated teams in the nation _ and
the only one that hasn't lost a game. The women figure to be in
good shape, considering no match has lasted longer than 1 hour, 28
minutes. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
