<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUSIEST-FAMILY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AMERICA'S BUSIEST FAMILY HAILS FROM TEXAS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By TERRY LEE GOODRICH 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Good thing the Chanceys were sitting down when they got the
news.
</P>
<P>
   The Denton family of four had taken a breather Tuesday morning
on a sofa in a New York hotel when a cordless telephone rang _ the
signal that they had won the title of America's Busiest Family.
</P>
<P>
   Confetti flew. Callie Chancey, 9, jumped up and down. Stunned
mom Karen Chancey exulted about one prize: housecleaning for a
year.
</P>
<P>
   ``What a blast!'' said dad Keith Chancey, youth minister at
Denton Bible Church. ``Who would have thought it?''
</P>
<P>
   They bested more than 200 families, who had telephoned contest
sponsor Siemens Cordless to describe their hectic lives.
</P>
<P>
   Siemens flew the Chanceys and other finalists _ a Nebraska
family and an Arizona family _ to the New York Marriott Marquis in
Times Square, where a judge questioned them. Then they waited _
each family left with a cordless telephone _ for the winner's phone
to ring.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Chanceys are amazing, not only because of their own
schedule, but because of college students living with them,'' said
judge Kathy Peel of Dallas, a family management expert. ``They have
people in their house all the time. But they've found a balance to
take care of themselves.''
</P>
<P>
   To go to New York, the family had to juggle school, sports,
theater, ballet and Keith's time with youths and families. During
the weeklong, expenses-paid trip, the Chanceys will sightsee,
including at what Cameron, 7, calls ``the Entire State Building.''
</P>
<P>
   The pampering will last a year. Other prizes are monthly in-home
meals by a chef and a cordless telephone system with four handsets.
</P>
<P>
   ``Keith's afraid the housecleaning is going to spoil me,'' Karen
Chancey said. ``But I say, `Bring it on!' ''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-27-00 2327EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
